benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/invoices - Retrieve account invoices

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios like TC01 (no query params), TC02 (date filters), TC03 (migration invoices), TC04 (unpaid invoices), TC05 (voided invoices), TC06 (audit info), TC07 (all filters combined), TC08 (no invoices), TC09 (unsupported params), TC10 (malformed accountId), TC11 (non-existent account), TC12 (missing auth), TC13 (invalid auth), TC14 (service down), TC15 (injection attempt), TC16 (large dataset), TC17 (slow dependency), TC18 (concurrent requests), TC19 (regression unpaid filter), TC20 (backward compatibility), TC21 (startDate after endDate), TC22 (extreme date range), TC23 (partial dates), TC24 (all boolean true), TC25 (no matching invoices), TC26 (large accountId), TC27 (XSS in params), TC28 (inconsistent downstream data), TC29 (API documentation accessibility).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for handling paginated responses or large datasets beyond TC16.
Authorization: No tests explicitly verify 403 Forbidden responses for unauthorized users.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios test system behavior under high request volume or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests check for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify correct handling of large datasets and response headers.
Include tests for unauthorized access (e.g., 403 Forbidden) to ensure proper authorization enforcement.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system stability under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior for GET responses.
